{"questionId":"11876","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate methods for finding definite integrals of powers of trigonometrical functions.</p>\n<p>Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{I_n} = \\int\\limits_0^{\\tfrac{\\pi }{2}} {{\\text{si}}{{\\text{n}}^n}} x\\,dx{\\text{,}}\\,\\,n \\in \\mathbb{N}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>I</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mfrac>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>si</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>n</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">N</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{J_n} = \\int\\limits_0^{\\tfrac{\\pi }{2}} {{\\text{co}}{{\\text{s}}^n}} x\\,dx{\\text{,}}\\,\\,n \\in \\mathbb{N}.\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>J</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mfrac>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>co</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>s</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">N</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>.</mo>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_n} = \\int\\limits_0^{\\tfrac{\\pi }{4}} {{\\text{ta}}{{\\text{n}}^n}} x\\,dx{\\text{,}}\\,\\,n \\in \\mathbb{N}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mi>n</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>0</mn>\n    <mrow>\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"false\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mfrac>\n          <mi>π</mi>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>ta</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>n</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>n</mi>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">N</mi>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find the exact values of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_{2}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_{3}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>3</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_2} = 1 - {T_0} = 1 - \\frac{\\pi }{4}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_3} = \\frac{1}{2} - {T_1} = \\frac{1}{2} - \\ln \\sqrt 2 \">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>ln</mi>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11876","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.3h","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, find the exact values of T 2 and T 3 .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.16—Integration by substitution, parts and repeated parts"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}